(1)
Commerce Street, south side, west from Seventh Ave., and across Bedford Street. This street at the far end makes a right angle bend northward, to terminate at Barrow Street. The 2½-story structures with the dormer windows are frame buildings and are separated by a 4-story tenement, that was formerly a factory.

May 19, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, in the opposite direction (eastward) as seen from a point west of Bedford Street and showing a 2½-story frame house at the S.W. corner of Bedford and Commerce Streets. This building bears No. 77 Bedford Street.

May 27, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.
